subSubSection.paragraph:
C. caracallae
has densely fasciculate, unbranched and shorter conidiophores [40-80 µm versus (28-)35.5-278(-340) μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] and slightly shorter conidia [50-75 μm versus (19-)26.5-100(-110.5) μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] ( Spegazzini 1910 ).
C. kikuchii
has unbranched and shorter conidiophores [45-200 x 3-6.5 µm versus (28-)35.5-278(-340) μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] and larger conidia [50-375 μm versus (19-)26.5-100(-110.5) μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] with up to 22 septa ( Hsieh and Goh 1990 ).
C. longispora
has unbranched, shorter and narrower conidiophores [5-30 x 1.5-3 µm versus (28-)35.5-278(-340) x (3.5-)4-5 μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] with inconspicuous conidiogenous loci and somewhat longer conidia [75-170 x 2-3.5 µm versus (19-)26.5-100(-110.5) μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] ( Chupp 1954 ).
C. vignigena
has paler, shorter and wider conidiophores [40-130 x 5-7(-10) µm versus (28-)35.5-278(-340) x (3.5-)4-5 μm in
C. vignae-subterraneae
] that are 0-3-septate, and wider conidia [(2.5-)4-6(-10) μm versus (2.5-)3-4 μm of
C. vignae-subterraneae
) ( Mulder and Holliday 1975 ).
